originalText.text: The end result was what mattered. Woman who seemed to be the boss, tried to bamboozle me out of cash like i was a blue haired fool. Went originally with a groupon for a gel manicure. I asked if i could get my nails a little longer, she slaps a extra $20 ontop of the groupon which i was ok with. Then because my phone died, i couldn't show her the groupon so i paid cash. Then i changed my mind and just wanted regular gel mani and regular pedi. She charged me $55 plus tip (she was very naggy about the tip as if she deserved one harrasing me the way she was). That was until i saw a deal on the wall "Gel mani and regualr pedi $45.00" and I asked her about that. She tried to deny that it was a deal and continued on about 55. Eventually i got get to give me the damn gel mani and pedi for 50 and $5 tip since she already had the $55 and she wanted a larger tip. She left me repeatedly to answer phones and I had to tell her off eventually. On the bright side, her co-workers were friendly and complimented my hair, I got to charge my phone and she did very good work on my nails. Its been a week already and no change so this will definitely last 2 weeks or more i feel. If you go in knowing what you want, and how much it costs everything else is pretty good about this place.
